history.content:
I'm a sophomore thinking of taking 152 next semester since 170 may not be offered... I was just wondering if enrollment would expand for 152 at all. I know it won't expand beyond room capacity, but I was wondering if the current enrollment capacity also reflects the room capacity fully, as I noticed some other classes are limiting enrollment to 70% capacity. Also, any advice for getting into upperdivision classes when not (yet) declared is welcome, including classes that may be helpful in the long run that aren't in the EECS department (so I can actually enroll to them).

Thanks!
history.subject: CS 152 Enrollment + general enrollment advice
